Sappi Heads for Biggest Two-Day Decline Since June 2009

-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 
2011-12-02T07:28:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-02/sappi-heads-for-biggest-two-day-decline-since-june-2009-1-.html
Sappi Ltd. (SAP)  is headed for its biggest
two-day decline since June 2009 in Johannesburg trading.  The stock fell as much as 70 cents, or 3.1 percent, to
22.40 rand, bringing its two-day decline to 9.6 percent. The
stock traded at 22.51 rand as of 9:27 a.m. local time.  The stock rose 7.7 percent on Nov. 30.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
